{"key":"post-11571656","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11571656</id>\n<content>A small pie tin will give small mushrooms because it's a small, thin substrate.&amp;nbsp; Fresh air is the number one pinning trigger.&amp;nbsp; That's why you &lt;b&gt;must&lt;/b&gt; mist or your substrate will dry out. The holes in a shotgun terrarium provide for fresh air, which in turn dries out your substrate.&amp;nbsp; That's how it's supposed to work. Get the substrate wet, and then let it dry out slightly again before misting.&amp;nbsp; This ebb and flow of moisture is what produces the best flushes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11571661</next>\n<prev>11571621</prev>\n<first>11571528</first>\n<last>11574810</last>\n<when>1259803481</when>\n<utime>12/03/09 03:24 AM</utime>\n</post>"}